annotation.TEXT: Grover!
I was trying to think if I needed to hit a shrine B-switch for a moment there, but no, I don't.
Now, remember that B-switch up in the sky here? Well, it's totally not needed for anything, so don't worry about it.
Using this white guy to remove one of the Wigglers is a good idea.
John!
James!
Millard!
Abraham!
There's those 5 stars I said I'd get back to. Just 4 remain, and they're in that side room near the end.
May as well get them on the way, since I'm heading back to the beginning to do stuff anyway. Also, I'm going to use this reset pipe right here, to refresh all B-switches.
Rutherford!
Obviously, don't kill all of the white guys over there, but it's okay to kill some of them.
Also, there's a couple of white duders buried here for some reason. Well, they're worth 500 points each for hammering them, so why not?
Excellent! Now, remember that maze with the P block I pointed out at one point during the initial run? This is that maze, and my goal is to reach the P block first.
Alright, here's the last thing that I absolutely need the broom for-- these stars up here.
And that's because I've got my broom!
Okay, next up is this tricky B-switch climbing segment. If I blow it here, I restart, because it'd take way too long I think to find a way to reset the B-switch and try again.
And yes, the game is a bit laggy here. That seems to happen when there's a lot of "platform dirt" around, so to speak. I still have no idea why.
Yes, I wanted to kill that Chomp. It's possible to fly to the stars above him, so there's no need to try drill stomp bouncing off of him.
Grover!
Okay, I'm certain I hit my target, so while I wait for the broom to fall, I'll take out the remaining duders here.
Okay, that blue guy wasn't in my way, fortunately. Also, most of the enemies down here are usually still alive, but they're not too much of a threat if I'm careful.
Okay, I've clobbered all the Thwomps over there, I believe. (They're the ones that took away my broom on my first run.)
Man, I'm stumbling so much here...
Unfortunately, that pipe down there doesn't actually work, so I've gotta retrace my steps through earlier parts of the level again.
Oh, whoops. I almost went the wrong way there. I want to fly up and to the right now, for a huge time-saver, which I thought of after failing by like 10 sec. that other time.
And of course, clear the path here like usual.
I'm glad I cleared the Thwomps out from here with hammer orbs earlier. Also, if you're fast, I think you can skip the B-switch in the Thwomp room, but I won't risk it now.
Anyway, I think I got sidetracked there. What were we talking about? Red Bull giving you wings? Ah, whatever.
Whoa, geez. Almost walked right into that guy. (One of my failures was actually due to me walking right into that particular guy.)
And that "stuff" I'm doing back here at the beginning is killing these green dudes, so that there's no chance of them sniping me as I'm on the home stretch later.
Alright, now the broom is merely just a convenience and an extra hit, and if I lose it now, the run isn't an automatic failure. Still, I'll try not to lose it.
Now, go down this way and hit the B-switch to the left here, watching out for the yellow guy, who sometimes jumps up to the ledge above.
Next, I like to hit one of the B-switches near the shrine, and get a few stars as I make my way back to the beginning.
Keep firing hammer orbs all over the place, and you'll likely kill many offscreen dudes, which is a good thing, because the more you kill now, the less you'll encounter later.
Also, the Punch-Out!! character Bald Bull hails from that country.
Come on. Don't waste time screwing up these simple jumps.
Maybe I should've sped up this part of the footage...
Andrew!
I'll be coming back with the broom later for the stars above there. Meanwhile, try to hammer some more dudes around here, including offscreen ones.
BTW, see that pipe above the checkpoint there? DO NOT enter it. It sends you to a much earlier part of the level. Guess what made me abort one of my attempts?
I'm sure it's possible to do it way faster than that, but I'm not trying for a flawless speedrun here.
Okay, that's good. Now to climb up to the shrine and then B-switch my way over to the broom room, just like I did during my first run.
And, just like before, go this way to collect 7 stars.
And now to retrace my steps.
Come on, open up already! I'm an impatient ordinary magician!
Alright, broom time!
James!
Martin!
There were Rexes here, but they hammered earlier, I guess. Now, DO NOT jump down towards the goal yet! The side room with the 4 stars is further left!
Okay, now I should be good to go.
There's certain key enemies that I hope I'll have killed by the time I get to where I'd encounter them normally later. Particularly Thwomps.
I like making sure I kill all the blue guys in the maze too, just for the heck of it.
John!
I'll be coming through here at least one additional time later, so clearing out an extra column of bricks isn't a bad idea.
BTW, there are no stray stars up in the sky in this level, which is nice.
Go up through here, since the path to the right is now blocked on the lower route.
How did that one guy bounce off the ceiling without dying?! Wow, that's weird. Usually, they don't survive being tossed into a ceiling...
Chester!
Also, be careful, as it appears to be possible to get hopelessly stuck if the B-switch expires while you're in that star room. (Fortunately, I never got trapped that way.)
Okay, after resetting this B-switch again, it's time for the next thing, and I'm going to want the help of the white duder that's in the P block as well.
No need to return to start unnecessarily, and it's a very nice amount of time saved.
9 attempts later...
Hmm... I could get on Rumia again now, and I would've, if I'd left more green guys alive to the right, but since I already killed all but 2 of them, Rumia's not needed again.
Get these green guys to aim this way so that I don't need to worry about dodging bullets while waiting for the green wall to get out of my way.
Nice. Just two green duders short of perfect there, and I'll deal with them later. (My best combo there on previous attempts got all but one of them.)
Excellent. Next, I should reset that B-switch for the next thing.
Zachary!
That B-switch is skippable if you're fast.
Looks like I didn't hammer every single green guy here earlier, but the Chomp was the important thing to get rid of here, since I can just fly to these stars.
Hmm... I think I only needed to screw the left screw there, but whatever.
So yeah, I've come back this way to get the higher-up stars here.
So, up next will be another boss level. How talkative will this boss be? Find out next time!
And that's it! I have now perfected this level! And with over 160 seconds to spare, too!
So, yeah, about Turkey... Well, Ankara is the capital.
John!
Actually, whoops. I've gotta refresh that B-switch. The nearest pipe I can do that with is over here.
Yep, told ya I'd be coming back this way. In addition, since I took the time to get certain stars in this direction earlier, I don't need any of the shrine B-switches anymore.
Alright, let's do this without wasting too much time. I've already had a would-be perfect fail by a matter of maybe 10 seconds.
For instance, I think if you punch Piston Honda's gut at just the right time just after he's finished dancing around the arena, he goes right down.
Obviously, screw this screw for later, and at this point, I like to go on the Rumia rampage, so that certain blue guys won't interfere with the next thing I want to do.
I actually came close to screwing up there. Be careful not to drill any column too far down.
Benjamin!
But, he's not the only one with a one-punch weakness. Several other boxers can be knocked down with a single punch under the right circumstances.
Andrew!
Now, there was another reason I wanted to return to the beginning, and it's because the miko suit maze caused me to skip some parts of the level, which have stars.
James!
Seriously, what was that? ...A failed duck jump, of course.
Alright, that's all 100! NOW, race to the goal!
Ulysses!
Now, quick, go out this way, and turn left. BTW, going right takes you to a pipe that sends you back to the start of the level, but there's nothing else of interest that way.
Whoops. My hammer barrage earlier missed one of those green guys. No big deal.
But then I wouldn't be able to talk about Turkey! I mean, Thanksgiving is approaching, after all.
I really should broom-smack the lingering green guy here. If I lose my broom now, the run is a failure, since I still need it for at least one more thing.
BTW, I'm going to use this reset pipe, just in case.
Upon getting to the P block, it's time to go nuts!
Killer combo! (26 hits, 196,500 points!)
Okay, I think I've gotten my act together, and I think I'm still doing okay, time-wise right now.
Franklin!
James!
Okay, now just like before, leave at least a couple alive, just in case I screw up the toss.
Whoa. I'd still kinda like to keep my broom, if at all possible.
In addition to those, you can fly up this passage just to the left to get some more.
Now, it is just barely possible to make it here without hitting the mole room's B-switch, if you move perfectly, but having more leeway is always nice.
Screw this screw down and kill this yellow guy, carefully. (I've died to him before.)
You know that guy, right? He's the one you can knock down with a single punch if you time it right during his Bull Charge.
Okay, now this blue guy, I'm not going to kill immediately. Instead, I want to use him to help me with this Chomp over here.
Yeah, there was no time to try anything else with that B-switch activation.
Yep, that white guy allowed me to hit that B-switch in the mole room from down here, giving me more time to go this way.
William!
Thomas!
I'm not worried about the time wasted on those guys. My progress so far has been faster than usual.
To be continued... Ze!
Haaahahahaha!!! Rain destruction down from the heavens on everyone!!!
These 3, and 4 more just a bit further down.
And here's 5 stars. Now, the pipe just above the leftmost star there takes you back to the start, but you can save time by getting in and out quick like this.
James!
Obviously, be careful of the blue guys. I've carelessly died to them a couple times already. Most vertical ones are easily stompable, so take advantage of that.
As for those stars just below, don't worry about them. They're reachable now, but I'm gonna come barrelling through that passage later anyway, so I'll get them then.
Alright, this time around, I'm pretty much heading to the goal now. There's only one side room left that I'll need to visit for stars, and that's near the end.
Jumping out here is the only way to escape the maze, and takes you to a later part of the level, near the "shriiine of the silver monkey".
And, if I had Rumia kill those remaining two, I'd get 100+200 points, instead of 500+500 for hammering them. Yeah, points aren't really important, but whatever.
